subNode:value.scalar:string: Display the pages requested by your visitors that have not been found.

pagenotfound` ( id_pagenotfound INTEGER UNSIGNED NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT, id_shop INTEGER UNSIGNED NOT NULL DEFAULT '1', id_shop_group INTEGER UNSIGNED NOT NULL DEFAULT '1', request_uri VARCHAR(256) NOT NULL, http_referer VARCHAR(256) NOT NULL, date_add DATETIME NOT NULL, PRIMARY KEY(id_pagenotfound), INDEX (`date_add`) ) ENGINE=
SELECT http_referer, request_uri, COUNT(*) as nb FROM `
The pages not found cache has been emptied.
Pages not found have been deleted.
You must use a .htaccess file to redirect 404 errors to the page "404.php"
Empty ALL pages not found for this period

A 404 error is an HTTP error code which means that the file requested by the user cannot be found. In your case it means that one of your visitors entered a wrong URL in the address bar or that you or another website has a dead link. When it is available, the referrer is shown so you can find the page which contains the dead link. If not, it means generally that it is a direct access, so someone may have bookmarked a link which doesn't exist anymore.
If your webhost supports .htaccess files, you can create one in the root directory of PrestaShop and insert the following line inside:
A user requesting a page which doesn't exist will be redirected to the following page.
This module logs access to this page.
